Bobooks API
1. Project Overview
Bobooks is a hyper-local textbook exchange platform designed specifically for students at the
University of Padua. It facilitates a trust-based marketplace where students can buy, sell, and
swap books without payment gateways, leveraging a real-time chat system to arrange physical
meetups.
Tech Stack:
Backend Framework: FastAPI (Python 3.12+)
Database: PostgreSQL 16 (Containerized via Docker)
ORM & Migrations: SQLAlchemy (Declarative Base)
Data Validation: Pydantic v2
Security: Passlib (bcrypt < 4.0.0), OAuth2 Password Bearer
Server: Uvicorn (ASGI)
