4. API Endpoints (Current Implementation)
The following endpoints are currently live and verified via Swagger UI ( http://
127.0.0.1:8000/docs ):
User Management
POST /users/ : Registers a new student. Accepts name, email, unipd_id, and password.
Securely hashes the password using bcrypt before persisting. Returns 201 Created .
GET /users/{user_id} : Fetches a public profile for a student by their ID. Used for viewing
seller profiles.
Authentication
POST /login : Standard OAuth2 login route. Accepts username (email) and password via
form data. Verifies against the database and currently returns a dummy bearer token.
5. Known Configurations & Quirks
Bcrypt Dependency: The application relies on bcrypt < 4.0.0 due to a known bug in
Passlib's internal sanity checks with newer bcrypt versions.
Pydantic Emails: The pydantic[email] extra is installed to validate student emails
seamlessly using the EmailStr type.
SQLAlchemy Table Creation: Tables are generated automatically on startup via
models.Base.metadata.create_all(bind=engine) . Future iterations should transition to
Alembic for migration management.
6. Development Roadmap & Next Steps
To take the project from this solid baseline to MVP, proceed with the following phases:
Phase 1: Real JWT Authentication
Replace the dummy token in auth.py with a real PyJWT implementation. Create a
get_current_user dependency so routes can identify who is making the request securely.
