Phase 2: The Marketplace (Listings)
Build the routers/listings.py file. Implement POST /listings/ (requiring a logged-in
user) and GET /listings/ (with query parameters to filter by subject_id ).
Phase 3: The Chat System (WebSockets)
Create routers/chat.py . Develop the REST endpoints to initialize a chat_room between a
buyer and seller. Then, implement FastAPI WebSockets to allow real-time message exchange
and database persistence for chat history.
Phase 4: Frontend Integration
Connect a frontend (e.g., React Native / Flutter for mobile, or React/Vue for web) to the live
Swagger endpoints. The API is entirely structured to feed standard JSON payloads to a modern
UI component architecture.